<subSubSection id="02A746BB94AE60F7F8CA959A494EDCB2" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3B719CD35069747DA222014BD58160F4" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="870AF2CA96C12D97EDE21DFC837CDFF5" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">
<bibRefCitation id="CD954A8F98F0863EB19C69E70661F9DB" author="Hubendick, B" journalOrPublisher="Fjaerde Serien" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 223" refId="B31" refString="Hubendick, B, 1951. Recent Lymnaeidae. Their variation, morphology, taxonomy, nomenclature and distribution. Kungliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar. Fjaerde Serien 3 (1): 1 - 223" title="Recent Lymnaeidae. Their variation, morphology, taxonomy, nomenclature and distribution. Kungliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar." volume="3" year="1951">Hubendick (1951)</bibRefCitation>
grouped most 
<taxonomicName id="9211D4DE40E1A9EC5832C6D11B720134" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E3BDD3B045400D49779426509746A7A" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. from the Near East (i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="BA09041BFB052127702F6ED7584ECA04" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tenera">
<emphasis id="558A3D192E32D2A03F4B5AA21630C19C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix tenera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B799E1C94DAF28C258422AB781A1EC3D" baseAuthorityName="Mousson" baseAuthorityYear="1874" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="euphratica">
<emphasis id="8D22CCBAA917EE6AE305562C41334A89" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix euphratica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<normalizedToken id="9166FD22547923A7F68B0EB45A08E02B" originalValue="«Mesopotamia»">&quot;Mesopotamia&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B3281A3C1F4599E6FCC6E6FC2E48DDA6" baseAuthorityName="Annandale &amp; Prashad" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bactriana">
<emphasis id="723FD1E4254B1D3A924A36E9FD96857E" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix bactriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Afghanistan, 
<taxonomicName id="45C858F1B9736718F245D7CCD54BCFD3" baseAuthorityName="Annandale &amp; Prashad" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gedrosiana">
<emphasis id="A1E8CE399C5CD52B896A03662D738F96" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix gedrosiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Iran, 
<taxonomicName id="C191B4A433F692047A3F73B299C44034" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rectilabrum">
<emphasis id="4D2B4CC5A6016B29C1F4F583AAB8F82E" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix rectilabrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Seistan and Baluchistan, 
<taxonomicName id="91078011781877218B35EA5115A7E737" baseAuthorityName="Issel" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="B7E281CF05198414F1F9EA8EE659F6DD" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Iran and 
<taxonomicName id="7684146D4DC78C2F34FFFC1BA467F37C" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="acuminata">
<emphasis id="2AF1B1D2BDDA4229331D59DAFEEC4F01" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix acuminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- (Bengal, India) under the palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="B49C6A912354EE80FA5C57E7EE8CBE22" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="auricularia">
<emphasis id="431A94B34617EBC7CA6A56C7EFA66DDD" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix auricularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but from Europe he lumped all 
<taxonomicName id="689697DC80D55E17F8CCE38FB7226521" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C5422A26A0B20886C9E66339B8B8904C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. 
<pageBreakToken id="6146B446753231A084F0178CA21AFD0C" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" start="start">together</pageBreakToken>
in three species. Today, five 
<taxonomicName id="0C52CD6A747912B41057E4F3F9B0A097" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9FD883CA582A82A2F7AC94742C10F8BE" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are known from Europe, confirmed by molecular (
<bibRefCitation id="F1646B34A2A99740B798BD003A562910" author="Pfenninger, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" publicationUrl="10.1186/1471-2148-6-100" refId="B49" refString="Pfenninger, M, Cordellier, M, Streit, B, 2006. Comparing the efficacy of morphologic and DNA-based taxonomy in the freshwater gastropod genus Radix (Basommatophora, Pulmonata). BiomedCentral Evolutionary Biology 14 pp. BMC Evolutionary Biology2006, 6:100., 10.1186/1471-2148-6-100" title="Comparing the efficacy of morphologic and DNA-based taxonomy in the freshwater gastropod genus Radix (Basommatophora, Pulmonata). BiomedCentral Evolutionary Biology 14 pp. BMC Evolutionary Biology 2006, 6: 100" url="10.1186/1471-2148-6-100" year="2006">Pfenninger et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="DBB5CE1E9B9F57D447487755EDD89796" author="Schniebs, K" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="657 - 678" refId="B53" refString="Schniebs, K, Gloeer, P, Vinarski, MV, Hundsdoerfer, AK, 2011. Intraspecific morphological and genetic variability in Radix balthica (Linnaeus 1758) (Gastropoda: Basommatophora: Lymnaeidae) with morphological comparison to other European Radix species. Journal of Conchology 40 (6): 657 - 678" title="Intraspecific morphological and genetic variability in Radix balthica (Linnaeus 1758) (Gastropoda: Basommatophora: Lymnaeidae) with morphological comparison to other European Radix species." volume="40" year="2011">Schniebs et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and anatomical studies (
<bibRefCitation id="A44E0656FD6CDA1D1B0EF413A729A09D" author="Gloeer, P" journalOrPublisher="Die Tierwelt Deutschlands" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B22" refString="Gloeer, P, 2002. Die Suesswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas. Bestimmungsschluessel, Lebensweise, Verbreitung. Die Tierwelt Deutschlands 73, 327 pp." title="Die Suesswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas. Bestimmungsschluessel, Lebensweise, Verbreitung." volume="73" year="2002">
<normalizedToken id="A8113FAC70F8466AA56E0FEBFE5E470E" originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Only a few species can be distinguished by the shells alone (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="AC42667935405CE40158FB69EEF97902" baseAuthorityName="Mighels" baseAuthorityYear="1843" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ampla">
<emphasis id="8948F86125F785EE0DEA7B91655C74E0" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix ampla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0502E058F33E1305ECB649F72B5476BA" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="auricularia">
<emphasis id="0A441D0C3F2DFA88CACFCF44F5C45016" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix auricularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Most species show a large morphological plasticity in the shape of the shell, so this character cannot be used for distinguishing species. 
<bibRefCitation id="E1B2B071C6908FCC501F5EF85916E9CD" author="Annandale, N" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="18 - 62" refId="B3" refString="Annandale, N, Prashad, B, 1919. The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan. Records of the Indian Museum 18: 18 - 62" title="The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan." volume="18" year="1919">Ananndale and Prashad (1919)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="35F0983CFB053AC9CCD31F3480B4F8EF" author="Annandale, N" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="137 - 189" refId="B4" refString="Annandale, N, Rao, HS, 1925. Materials for a revision of the recent Indian Lymnaeidae (Mollusca Pulmonata). Records of the Indian Museum 27: 137 - 189" title="Materials for a revision of the recent Indian Lymnaeidae (Mollusca Pulmonata)." volume="27" year="1925">Annandale and Rao (1923)</bibRefCitation>
provided anatomical data of 
<taxonomicName id="069B84C4AB977E468674445CD52FCA6B" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="174F832CB482A1EDAD8E37CE03E9724D" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., but these drawings are not suitable enough to identify the 
<taxonomicName id="AD4BFD67B3DB69191175E0A6D107408C" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FBF9942CF30272DDA4109197BCEFBFEA" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. found by us in Iran. The diagnostic features and taxonomic relationship of the Iranian 
<taxonomicName id="009829AA2BC410014605056C6A245561" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="24A3B0EBBA642959B453D66656D601E2" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species require further revision and particularly the application of molecular techniques with topotypes of the species. The following list of 
<taxonomicName id="74FEE605831A0742B222D7497B6CA9C4" authorityName="Montfort" authorityYear="1810" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" genus="Radix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Basommatophora" pageId="14" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="44CBD8DCC329E8440100EC90ED923CE3" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="25">Radix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species contains the hitherto recorded nominal species, their taxonomic status remains to be explored.
</paragraph>
